#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:21
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preparing for installation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:30
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter explains how to make the data accessible for installation, "
"install &productname; using different methods, and prepare and use the IPL "
"of the &productname; installation system. The chapter also provides "
"information about network configuration and network installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:38
#, no-c-format
msgid "Making the installation data available"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:39
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section provides detailed information about making the &productname; "
"&zseries; installation data accessible for installation. Depending on your "
"computer and system environment, choose between NFS or FTP installation. If "
"you are running Microsoft Windows workstations in your environment, you can "
"use the Windows network (including the SMB protocol) to install "
"&productname; on your &zseries; system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:48
#, no-c-format
msgid "IPL from DVD"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to IPL from DVD and use the DVD as the installation medium. "
"This is very convenient if you have restrictions setting up an installation "
"server providing installation media over your network. The prerequisite is "
"an FCP-attached SCSI DVD Drive."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "No installation from hard disk"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is not possible to perform installation from a hard disk by putting the "
"content of the DVD to a partition on a DASD."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using a Linux workstation or &productname; DVD"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:65
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use a Linux workstation in your computer environment to provide the "
"installation data to the &zseries; installation process by NFS or FTP. If "
"the Linux workstation runs &productname;, you can set up an installation "
"server (NFS or FTP) using the &yast; <guimenu>Installation Server</guimenu> "
"module as described in <xref linkend=\"sec-deployment-instserver-sles9\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting mounted devices with NFS"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Exporting the file system root ( <filename>/</filename> ) does not "
"automatically export the mounted devices, such as DVD. Therefore, you need "
"to explicitly name the mount point in <filename>/etc/exports</filename> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:81
#, no-c-format
msgid "/media/dvd  *(ro)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:82
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After changing this file, restart the NFS server with the command "
"<command>sudo systemctl restart nfsserver</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:87
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Setting up an FTP server on a Linux system involves the installation and "
"configuration of server software like <package>vsftpd</package> . If you are "
"using &productname;, refer to <xref linkend=\"cha-ftp\"/> for installation "
"instructions. Downloading the installation data via anonymous login is not "
"supported, therefore you need to configure the FTP server to support user "
"authentication."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:97
#, no-c-format
msgid "&productname; on DVD"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:98
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first installation medium of the &productname; for &zseries; contains a "
"bootable Linux image for Intel-based workstations and an image for &zseries;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:103
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For Intel-based workstations, boot from this medium. When prompted, choose "
"the desired answer language and keyboard layout and select <guimenu>Start "
"rescue system</guimenu> . You need at least 64&nbsp;MB RAM for this. No disk "
"space is needed, because the entire rescue system resides in the "
"workstation's RAM. This approach requires setting up the networking of the "
"workstation manually."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For &zseries;, IPL your LPAR/VM guest from this medium as described in <xref "
"linkend=\"sec-prep-ipling-lpar-dvd\"/> . After entering your network "
"parameters, the installation system treats the medium as the source of "
"installation data. Because &zseries; cannot have an X11-capable terminal "
"attached directly, choose between VNC or SSH installation. SSH also provides "
"a graphical installation by tunneling the X connection through SSH with "
"<command>ssh -X</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using a Microsoft Windows workstation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use a Microsoft Windows workstation on your network to make the "
"installation media available. The easiest way to do this is to use the SMB "
"protocol. Make sure to activate <guimenu>SMB over TCP/IP</guimenu> as this "
"enables the encapsulation of SMB packages into TCP/IP packages. Find details "
"in the Windows online help or other Windows-related documentation that "
"covers networking."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:133
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using SMB"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:134
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To make the installation media available with SMB, insert the "
"&usbflashdrive; with &installmedia; into the USB port of the Windows "
"workstation. Then create a new share using the &usbflashdrive;'s letter and "
"make it available for everyone in the network."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:143
#, no-c-format
msgid "The installation path in &yast; can be:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"smb://<replaceable>DOMAIN</replaceable>;<replaceable>USER</replaceable>:"
"<replaceable>PW</replaceable>@<replaceable>SERVERNAME</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>SHAREPATH</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:147
#, no-c-format
msgid "Where the placeholders mean:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:152
#, no-c-format
msgid "<replaceable>DOMAIN</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:155
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional workgroup or active directory domain."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:161
#, no-c-format
msgid "<replaceable>USER</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:163
#, no-c-format
msgid "<replaceable>PW</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:166
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional user name and password of a user who can access this server and its "
"share."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:173
#, no-c-format
msgid "<replaceable>SERVERNAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:176
#, no-c-format
msgid "The name of the server that hosts the share(s)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:182
#, no-c-format
msgid "<replaceable>SHAREPATH</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:185
#, no-c-format
msgid "The path to the share(s)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:194
#, no-c-format
msgid "With NFS"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:195
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Refer to the documentation provided with the third party product that "
"enables NFS server services for your Windows workstation. The "
"&usbflashdrive; containing the &installmedia; medium must be in the "
"available NFS path."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:203
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using FTP"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:204
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Refer to the documentation provided with the third-party product that is "
"enabling FTP server services on your Windows workstation. The "
"&usbflashdrive; containing the &installmedia; medium must be in the "
"available FTP path."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The FTP server that is bundled with certain Microsoft Windows releases "
"implements only a subset of the FTP commands, and it is not suitable for "
"providing the installation data. In this case, use a third-party FTP server "
"that offers the required functionality."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:218
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using an FCP-attached SCSI DVD drive"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:219
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After you IPLed from the SCSI DVD as described in <xref linkend=\"sec-prep-"
"ipling-lpar-dvd\"/> , the installation system uses the DVD as the "
"installation medium. In this case, you do not need the installation media on "
"an FTP, NFS, or SMB server. However, you need the network configuration data "
"for your &productname;, because you must set up the network during the "
"installation to perform a graphical installation via VNC or by X."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:232
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using a Cobbler server for zPXE"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:233
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"IPLing from the network requires a Cobbler server to provide the kernel, "
"initrd, and the installation data. Preparing the Cobbler server requires the "
"following steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:240
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<xref xrefstyle=\"select:label nopage\" linkend=\"sec-prep-makeavail-zpxe-"
"cobbler-import\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:245
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<xref xrefstyle=\"select:label nopage\" linkend=\"sec-prep-makeavail-zpxe-"
"cobbler-add-distro\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:250
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<xref xrefstyle=\"select:label nopage\" linkend=\"sec-prep-makeavail-zpxe-"
"cobbler-profile\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:255
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<xref xrefstyle=\"select:label nopage\" linkend=\"sec-prep-makeavail-zpxe-"
"cobbler-system\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:261
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing the installation data"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:262
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Importing the media requires the installation source to be available on the "
"Cobbler server&mdash;either from &usbflashdrive; or from a network source. "
"Run the following command to import the data:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:267
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;cobbler import --path=<replaceable>PATH</replaceable><co xml:id="
"\"co-cobbler-import-path\"/> --name=<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable><co "
"xml:id=\"co-cobbler-import-dirname\"/> --arch=s390x"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:270
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mount point of the installation data."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:275
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A string identifying the imported product, for example <quote>sles15_s390x</"
"quote> . This string is used as the name for the subdirectory where the "
"installation data is copied to. On a Cobbler server running on &sle; this is "
"<filename>/srv/www/cobbler/ks_mirror/<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable></"
"filename> . This path may be different if Cobbler runs on another operating "
"system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:287
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding a distribution"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:288
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Adding a distribution allows Cobbler to provide the kernel and the initrd "
"required to IPL via zPXE. Run the following command on the Cobbler server to "
"add &productname; for &zseries;:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:293
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;cobbler distro add --arch=s390 --breed=suse --name="
"\"<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable>\"<co xml:id=\"co-cobbler-add-"
"identifier\"/> \\\n"
"  --os-version=sles15<co xml:id=\"co-cobbler-add-os\"/> \\\n"
"  --initrd=/srv/www/cobbler/ks_mirror/<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable>/"
"boot/s390x/initrd<co xml:id=\"co-cobbler-add-initrd\"/> \\\n"
"  --kernel=/srv/www/cobbler/ks_mirror/<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable>/"
"boot/s390x/linux<co xml:id=\"co-cobbler-add-kernel\"/> \\\n"
"  --kopts=\"install=http://cobbler.&exampledomain;/cobbler/ks_mirror/"
"<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable>\"<co xml:id=\"co-cobbler-add-server\"/"
">\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:301
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Unique identifier for the distribution, for example <quote>&slsa; "
"&productnumber; &zseries;</quote> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:307
#, no-c-format
msgid "Operating system identifier. Use <literal>sles15</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:312
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Path to the initrd. The first part of the path ( <filename>/srv/www/cobbler/"
"ks_mirror/<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable>/</filename> ) depends on the "
"location of the imported data and the subdirectory name you chose when "
"importing the installation data."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:320
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Path to the kernel. The first part of the path ( <filename>/srv/www/cobbler/"
"ks_mirror/<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable>/</filename> ) depends on the "
"location of the imported data and the subdirectory name you chose when "
"importing the installation data."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:328
#, no-c-format
msgid "URL to the installation directory on the Cobbler server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:335
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adjusting the profile"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:336
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Adding a distribution (see <xref linkend=\"sec-prep-makeavail-zpxe-cobbler-"
"add-distro\"/> ) automatically generates a profile with the corresponding "
"<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable> . Use the following command to make a "
"few required adjustments:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:343
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;cobbler distro edit \\\n"
"--name=<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable><co xml:id=\"co-cobbler-profile-"
"name\"/> --os-version=sles10<co xml:id=\"co-cobbler-profile-os\"/> --ksmeta="
"\"\"<co xml:id=\"co-cobbler-profile-meta\"/>\n"
"--kopts=\"install=http://cobbler.example.com/cobbler/ks_mirror/"
"<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable>\"<co xml:id=\"co-cobbler-profile-opts"
"\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:348
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Identifier for the profile. Use the string specified when added the "
"distribution."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Operating system version. Distribution to which the profile should apply. "
"Use the string specified with <option>--name=<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</"
"replaceable></option> in the importing step."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:362
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Option required for templating Kickstart files. Since it is not used for "
"&suse;, leave it empty."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:368
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Space-separated list of kernel parameters. It must include at least the "
"<literal>install</literal> parameter."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:376
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding systems"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:377
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The last step is to add systems to the Cobbler server. This step must be "
"performed for every &zseries; guest that should boot via zPXE. Guests are "
"identified by their z/VM user ID (in the following example, the ID "
"<quote>linux01</quote> ). Note that the ID must be lowercase. To add a "
"system, run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:384
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;cobbler system add --name=linux01 --hostname=linux01.example."
"com \\\n"
"--profile=<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable> --interface=qdio \\\n"
"--ip-address=&wsIVip; --subnet=&subnetII;.255 --netmask=&subnetmask; \\\n"
"--name-servers=&dnsip; --name-servers-search=&exampledomain; \\\n"
"--gateway=&routerintipII; --kopts=\"<replaceable>KERNEL_OPTIONS</replaceable>"
"\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:389
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <option>--kopts</option> option allows you to specify the kernel and "
"installation parameters that are usually specified in the parmfile. Specify "
"the parameters using the following format: <replaceable>PARAMETER1=VALUE1 "
"PARAMETER2=VALUE2</replaceable> . The installer prompts for missing "
"parameters. For a fully-automated installation, you need to specify all "
"parameters for networking, DASDs and provide an &ay; file. Below is an "
"example for a guest equipped with an OSA interface using the same network "
"parameters as above."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:399
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"--kopts=\" \\\n"
"AutoYaST=http://&exampledomainip;.5/autoinst.xml \\\n"
"Hostname=linux01.example.com \\\n"
"Domain=&exampledomain; \\\n"
"HostIP=&wsIVip; \\\n"
"Gateway=&routerintipII; \\\n"
"Nameserver=&dnsip; \\\n"
"Searchdns=&exampledomain; \\\n"
"InstNetDev=osa; \\\n"
"Netmask=&subnetmask; \\\n"
"Broadcast=&subnetII;.255 \\\n"
"OsaInterface=qdio \\\n"
"Layer2=0 \\\n"
"PortNo=0 \\\n"
"ReadChannel=0.0.0700 \\\n"
"WriteChannel=0.0.0701 \\\n"
"DataChannel=0.0.0702 \\\n"
"DASD=600\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:420
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installing from a &usbflashdrivecap; of the HMC"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:421
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Installation of &productname; on &zseries; servers usually requires a "
"network installation source. If this requirement cannot be fulfilled, &sls; "
"allows you to use the &usbflashdrive; of the Hardware Management Console "
"(HMC) as an installation source for installation on an LPAR."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:427
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To perform installation from the &usbflashdrive; of the HMC, proceed as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:433
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add <option>install=hmc:/</option> to the <filename>parmfile</filename> (see "
"<xref linkend=\"sec-appdendix-parm\"/> ) or kernel options."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:439
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the manual-mode installation using <filename>linuxrc</filename> , choose "
"<emphasis role=\"italic\">Start Installation</emphasis> , then <emphasis "
"role=\"italic\">Installation</emphasis> , and then <emphasis role=\"italic"
"\">Hardware Management Console</emphasis> . The installation medium must be "
"in the HMC."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:449
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure network"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:450
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before starting the installation, specify a network configuration in "
"<filename>linuxrc</filename> . You cannot do this via boot parameters, and "
"it is very likely that you will need network access. In <filename>linuxrc</"
"filename> , go to <emphasis role=\"italic\">Start Installation</emphasis> , "
"then choose <emphasis role=\"italic\">Network Setup</emphasis> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:460
#, no-c-format
msgid "Linux system must boot first"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:461
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before granting access to the media in the &usbflashdrive; of the HMC, wait "
"until the Linux system is booted. IPLing can disrupt the connection between "
"the HMC and the LPAR. If the first attempt to use the described method "
"fails, you can grant the access and retry the option <option>HMC</option> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:470
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installation repository"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:471
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &usbflashdrive; is not kept as an installation repository, as the "
"installation is a one-time procedure. If you need an installation "
"repository, register and use the online repository."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:481
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installation types"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:482
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section describes &productname; installation steps for each "
"installation mode. When the preparation steps described in the previous "
"chapters have been completed, follow the overview of the desired "
"installation mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:488
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As described in <xref linkend=\"sec-prep-makeavail\"/> , there are three "
"different installation modes for Linux on &zseries;: LPAR, z/VM, and KVM "
"guest installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:494
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overview of an LPAR installation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:496
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Prepare the devices needed for installation. See <xref linkend=\"sec-prep-"
